      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey can u summarize this news bit for me? i just wanna know the pros and cons of that new energy bill they're talking about in pa. \n\n\"The Keystone State Legislature has introduced the 'Energy Future Act,' a sweeping package aimed at restructuring state energy subsidies. The bill proposes a significant shift, redirecting $500 million in annual subsidies from traditional coal-fired power plants toward the development of large-scale solar and wind farms. Proponents of the bill argue that the move is essential for meeting state climate goals and fostering a modern clean energy economy. Conversely, critics express concern over the potential for rising electricity costs for consumers and the immediate economic impact on coal mining communities in western PA, which rely heavily on the industry for stable employment.\"",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
